re I'm getting aaxp faster than I did prior to PoP's release. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=363562" target="top">Shazar Oom, 61 Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqheroes.com" target="top">Heroes of Luclin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dandaithemage>Dandaithemage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 3:05:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7899.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The best expansion yet...</span><hr size=1> I honestly feel this is the best expansion since Everquest was released.  The items fall short of what was expected, atleast in the first couple tiers, but the content is absolutely wonderful.  You get the feeling you're doing something that contributes to an ultimate story line, not just grinding experience and getting phat lewtz.  Sure you can stay at level 60 and solo and enjoy the game all fine, but I suggest getting in a decent guild, just a group of friends that are 55+ and enjoy your travels to the planes.  Everything in the first tier planes except for the big bosses only require two groups, three at the most.  Parchment drops are rare in tier 1, but uncommon in tier 2 and spectral parchments drop like rain in the Halls on Honor.<br>
